This assumes you already have vscodde installed. 

when first installing VSCode, to run javascript 

create a file named index.html or something with .html

Then add extension html preview
https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=tht13.html-preview-vscode

Write some basic html like this

<html>
    <head>
        <title>Hello World</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Hello World</p>
    </body>
</html>


Press ctrl+k then press v and you'll see a sidebar pop up. 

Then press ctrl+shift+v to run the html 

You should see Hello World pop up in the side bar. 

Now you are ready to code! 
